<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Commercial Ship Kidnaped in N. E. Somalia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOGADISHU, October 1 (xinhua) -- Somali gunmen in the
northeastern port of Bossaso have kdnapedSomali commercial
vessel "Nur Star" heading for Yeman, informed sources said in
Mogadishu Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Hassan Aden Gelle, representative of the owner of the ship,
told reporters that six gunmen stormed into the ship Tuesday and
forced its captain to sail it into the main sea. The ship was
taken away as it was getting ready for taking goats and sheep to
Yemen for a commercial purpose.
</P>
<P>
Gelle said the gunmen have wounded one of the crew and threw
six others off the ship at seashores off Habo village, about 80
kilometers east of Bossaso. The six crew members were rescued by
fishermen on small boats.
</P>
<P>
The ship is owned by Somali businessman Mohamed Abdullahi Nur
from northwestern regions, while the kidnappers are from Majerten
clan which is very popular in the sea piracy business along the
northeastern coasts of the country.
</P>
<P>
The reason for the kidnapping is unknown. But sources said the
gunmen have demanded a ransom of 100,000 U.S. Dollars in return
for the release of the ship. 
</P>
</TEXT>
