<HEADLINE> EU Inflation Drops to 1.3% in August </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, October 1 (Xinhua) -- The European Union annual
inflation rate decreased from 1.5 percent in July to 1.3 percent
in August, Eurostat reported on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The Luxembourg-based statistical bureau of the European
community said that inflation for the 11-nation euro zone also
dropped, from 1.4 percent in July to 1.2 percent in August.
</P>
<P>
The highest inflation was posted by Greece at 4.7 percent while
France and Sweden both had the lowest inflation rate at 0.6
percent.
</P>
<P>
Compared with a month earlier, Eurostat added, inflation
decreased in 12 of the 15 European Union member states, increased
in two and remained stable in one.
</P>
<P>
Ireland had the largest relative increase in inflation rates
compared with a year earlier. Rates in that country rose from 0.6
percent to 3.0 percent.
</P>
<P>
Sweden witnessed the largest relative decrease from 2.1 percent
to 0.6 percent in the same period of time. 
</P>
</TEXT>
