<HEADLINE> Zambia Calls for Employing Local People </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, October 1 (Xinhua) -- Zambian Labor and Social
Security Minister Peter Machungwa Thursday criticized some
employers for not utilizing the services of local human resources
practitioners.
</P>
<P>
Opening the first annual convention of the Zambia Institute of
Human Resources Management (ZIHRM) here in Lusaka, the minister
said the employers do not accept the idea of maintaining a human
resources department with a Zambian employed as human resources
practitioner.
</P>
<P>
"The human resource is one of the important factors in the
production process. Its management, therefore, is crucial to the
success of any enterprise," said Machungwa.
</P>
<P>
He complained that some new employers have brought in their
own human resources practitioners or consultants from their own
countries of origin, who in most cases, are not registered with
the institutions concerned.
</P>
<P>
The minister urged workers of Zambia, employers and
organizations concerned with labor matters and the human
resources management and industrial relations fields in
particular, to exercise the highest possible degree of
discipline.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the maintenance of industrial democracy and good
labor-management relations in the work place lies in an effective
preventive mediation and conciliation machinery.
</P>
<P>
Machungwa advocated the principle of give-and-take, describing
it very important in maintaining industrial peace. 
</P>
</TEXT>
