<HEADLINE> Lebanon, Syria to Hold Summit on Lebanon's </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, October 1 (Xinhua) -- Lebanese Interior Minister Michel
Al-Murr said on Thursday that Lebanon and Syria will hold a summit
within 10 days in Damascus to discuss Lebanon's presidential
elections.
</P>
<P>
Al-Murr made the remarks at a ceremony to mark the
International Day for the Elderly, the official National News
Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Lebanon and Syria, which maintains 40,000 troops in Lebanon as
peacekeepers, agree to coordinate stances on key issues.
</P>
<P>
Lebanese Foreign Minister Fares Boueiz said on Tuesday that
Syrian President Hafez al-Assad holds the key to Lebanon's
presidential elections due late this month.
</P>
<P>
The nine-year term of the Lebanese incumbent president, Elias
Hrawi, expires on October 24 when a new president will be elected
by the parliament.
</P>
<P>
A number of prestigious politicians have the intention to run
for the presidency.
</P>
<P>
Lebanese media have said the proposed summit would determine a
presidential candidate and the election process. 
</P>
