<HEADLINE> Chechen Government Dismissed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, October 1 (Xinhua) -- The Chechen government was
entirely dismissed by its president Aslan Maskhadov on Thursday,
according to the Interfax news agency.
</P>
<P>
Maskhadov told the government ministers that they were
dismissed from their posts, but they will remain in office until
the new cabinet is formed.
</P>
<P>
The dismissal order applies also to the heads of all agencies,
organizations and republican boards, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The leader of the break-away republic said that none of the
deputy prime ministers will be chosen as prime minister, and the
offices of first deputy prime ministers have been abolished.
</P>
<P>
Maskhadov praised the Road Transport Minister Nuzhden Daayev
and the Food and Agriculture Minister Lom-Ali Alsultanov for their
good performance; and criticized the construction and economic
ministries and the oil ministry.
</P>
<P>
According to the Chechen president, some of the new ministers
have been chosen, and the new government is expected to be rebuilt
early next week.
</P>
<P>
Maskhadov has been being the Chechen president since January
17, 1997, after the Russian Federation and the break-away republic
signed an agreement on peaceful settlement of the Chechen issue in
August, 1996. 
</P>
