<HEADLINE> EU Forms Working Group on Russia Crisis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, October 2 (Xinhua) -- The European Commission said on
Friday it had formed a consulting group mandated to work out
concrete recommendations within a month on how to help Russia out
of its financial crisis.
</P>
<P>
The group, which is scheduled to start next week, is expected
to examine the scope for improving coordination and more
accurately targeting policies of the European Commission and the
European Bank for Reconstruction and Development (EBRD).
</P>
<P>
The focus will be on areas such as restructuring of the banking
sector, giving support to small and medium-sized enterprises and
strengthening the investment climate throughout Russia.
</P>
<P>
The targeted initiatives recommended by the group will be
implemented in consultation with the World Bank and other
international financial institutions, a commission spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
The consulting group was formed after a meeting on Thursday
between EBRD President Horst Koehler and European Finance
Commissioner Yves-Thibault de Silguy.
</P>
<P>
European External Relations Commissioner Hans van den Broek
also agreed on the formation of the group. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
