<HEADLINE> Vietnam's 1st Telecommunications Satellite to Be Launched in 2001 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, October 2 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam's first telecommunications
satellite (Vinasat) will be launched in the second quarter of
2001, Vietnam News Agency (VNA) reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
A pre-feasibility study to this effect was approved by the
prime minister recently, VNA said.
</P>
<P>
Under the pre-feasibility study, the Vietnam Posts and
Telecommunications Corporation will be in charge of the project to
launch Vinasat.
</P>
<P>
The work will include the launching and operation of Vinasat,
the building and installation of ground satellite stations.
</P>
<P>
The ministries of national defense and public security, the
central television station and other relevant agencies will be
responsible for the ground stations serving their purposes.
</P>
<P>
According to VNA, a national steering board of the Vinasat
project will be set up with a deputy prime minister as director.
</P>
<P>
Under the project, which will cost approximately 400 million
U.S. dollars, Vinasat will be put into service in the fourth
quarter of 2001. 
</P>
