<HEADLINE> Israel Again Seals off Palestinian Territories </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, October 2 (Xinhua) -- The Israeli Defense Force
(IDF) imposed another total closure on The West Bank and Gaza
Strip for fear of possible terrorist attacks, it was officially
announced here Friday.
</P>
<P>
The closure started at 2:00 p.m. local time (1200 GMT) Friday
and will last till next Tuesday, the announcement said.
</P>
<P>
The IDF made this decision based on the reports that during the
Israel's Succot holidays (celebrating harvest), the Palestinian
Islamic Resistance Movement (Hamas) would carry out attacks
against targets in Israel, it said.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli defense establishment discussed security situation
in the territories and decided to get prepared for eventualities.
Whether the total closure would continue after next Tuesday will
be decided by IDF, the announcement said.
</P>
<P>
Total closure means closing all checkpoints, passes and
crossing points between Israel and the Palestinian territories,
banning Palestinians from entering into Israel and shutting down
all business including trade and transportations between the two
sides.
</P>
<P>
Following the IDF's killing of two Hamas members near West Bank
town of Hebron on September 10 and other shooting incidents at the
territories, confrontations and clashes between the Palestinians
and Israelis in the West Bank and Gaza had never been stopped.
</P>
<P>
Hamas vowed to avenge the killing of its members on Israelis.
Two grenades were thrown at a IDF jeep in Hebron Wednesday,
injuring 14 soldiers and 11 Palestinians.
</P>
<P>
On Friday, small scale clashes between Palestinians and Israeli
soldiers occurred in Hebron, but no injuries were reported.
</P>
</TEXT>
