<HEADLINE> Albanian New Cabinet Formed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, October 2 (Xinhua) -- Albanian President Rexhep Meidani
issued a decree on Friday approving a new 19-member government led
by Prime Minister Pandeli Majko.
</P>
<P>
Majko said at a news conference that the new cabinet, including
17 ministers, was formed by the ruling five-party coalition and
two non-party representatives.
</P>
<P>
The government started operating immediately after it was sworn
into office Friday afternoon in the presidential mansion, he added.
</P>
<P>
Majko also announced three urgent priorities for the
government: to stablize the situation as soon as possible; to
stage dialogues with the opposition and try to jointly have a new
constitution approved; and to cooperate with the international
community to solve the Kosovo crisis.
</P>
<P>
Majko finalized the cabinet list after two-days of
consultations with leaders of the five coalition parties.
</P>
<P>
Former Prime Minister Fatos Nano suddenly announced his
resignation on Monday. President Meidani nominated Majko on
Tuesday as the prime minister and directed him to form a new
government. 
</P>
