<HEADLINE> Hearts Appeal over Mallorca Goalposts </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, October 2 (Xinhua) -- Scottish club Hearts have
appealled to UEFA over the height of the goalposts at Thursday's
European Cup Winners' Cup match against Spanish club Mallorca.
</P>
<P>
Hearts, who drew 1-1 to go out 2-1 on aggregate, said the UEFA
delegate at the match found that one of the goalposts at each end
was too high due to the uneven pitch.
</P>
<P>
"We have recived an official protest about the size of the
goalposts," UEFA spokeswoman Tania Baima said on Friday.
</P>
<P>
"The matter will be dealt with by the Control and Disciplinary
Committee on October 8 in Geneva."
</P>
<P>
The UEFA spokeswoman pointed out that Thursday's incident was
not unique.
</P>
<P>
"The same thing happened last year in a match between Spartak
Moscow and Sion and the decision was to replay the match," she
said.
</P>
<P>
Hearts chairman Leslie Deans told local press on Friday: "We
only want to see fair play and the ball is now in UEFA's court."
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
