<HEADLINE> China Wins Mixed Doubles at Asian Table Tennis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, October 2 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Wang Liqin and Wang Nan
outwitted their South Korean opponents in straight sets to take
the mixed doubles title of the 14th Asian Table Tennis
Championships in Osaka on Friday.
</P>
<P>
This was the third gold medal won by the Chinese paddlers at
the current championships as they had harvested the men's and
women's team titles on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The second-seeded Chinese pair, who eliminated two Korean
pairs in their previous two rounds, enjoyed their upperhands
again the finals by beating Lee Chul-Seung and Ryu Ji-Hye of
South Korea 21-7, 21-15.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese two Wangs jumped ahead at 6-0 in the beginning and
never looked back to seal off the match in merely 20 minutes.
</P>
<P>
Earlier in the day, the Chinese pair defeated Seoul Olympic
champion Yoo Nam-Kyu and Lee Eun-Sil in the quarter-finals and
Park Sang-Joon and Park Hae-Jung in the semi-finals. 
</P>
