<HEADLINE> Marxist Bookstore Opens in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 2 (Xinhua) -- A bookstore selling Marxist
works opened in Beijing, the Chinese capital, on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The Gongming Chuangxin Bookstore, or Resonance and Creativeness
Bookstore, the first of its kind in China, is located near the
downtown Xidan commercial center.
</P>
<P>
"The shop features books on Marxism, Leninism, Mao Zedong
Thought and Deng Xiaoping Theory," according to owner Fan
Qiangming.
</P>
<P>
"Our goal is to spread Marxism and create a new spirit for the
Chinese nation," said Fan.
</P>
<P>
This year marks the 180th birth anniversary of Karl Marx and
the 150th anniversary of publication of the Communist Manifesto.
</P>
<P>
"This year also marks the 100th anniversary of the spread of
Marxism in China, and the 20th anniversary of China's reform and
opening to the outside world," according to Fan.
</P>
<P>
"I opened the store during the National Day holiday to promote
the inheritance and development of Marxism," said Fan.  
</P>
</TEXT>
