<TEXT>
<P>
DUNHUANG(Gansu Province), October 2 (Xinhua) -- An
expeditionary team departed Dunhuang today to begin a 10-day
desert trek along the legendary Silk Road.
</P>
<P>
The team of 55 tourists from Hong Kong and Guangdong left
Dunhuang, a famous Buddhist city on the ancient trade route, bound
for Turpan in the Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
The team will traverse the mysterious Lop Nor Region, home to
the prosperous Buddhist city of Loulan which disappeared some
2,000 years ago.  
