<HEADLINE> HKSAR Signs Air Services Agreement With Austria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, October 2 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (HKSAR) Friday signed an air services
agreement with Austria.
</P>
<P>
Secretary for Economic Services Stephen Ip signed the agreement
on behalf of the HKSAR Government while State Secretary for
Foreign Affairs Benita Ferrero-Waldner signed on behalf of the
Austrian Government.
</P>
<P>
Ip said Hong Kong and Austria have established close links in
trade, investment, business and tourism for many years. Direct air
services have played a vital role in promoting these links.
</P>
<P>
The Air Services Agreement will provide a legal framework for
continued development of the services, said Ip.
</P>
<P>
According to Ip, the agreement is the first of its kind signed
by Hong Kong after the new Hong Kong International Airport
commenced commercial operation on July 6.
</P>
<P>
"The new airport provides a significant increase in capacity
and operational flexibility for us to expand our air links with
the rest of the world. This will help to maintain Hong Kong's
status as an international and regional aviation center," he said.
</P>
<P>
The HKSAR/Austrian air services agreement is the 31st signed by
Hong Kong. 
</P>
</TEXT>
