<DOCNO> XIE19981002.0114 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> French-Nigerian Company to Develop Nigeria's </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, October 2 (Xinhua) -- ELF Petroleum Nigeria Ltd., a
French-Nigerian joint venture, is seeking about one billion U.S.
Dollars in the international finance market to develop a
mega-oilfield of Amenam, The Guardian newspaper reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
The development of Amenam, which is located southeast
off-shore of the Niger Delta will enable ELF to increase its
daily output from 120,000 to 200,000 barrels, raising its ranking
from fifth to the fourth largest oil producer in this major
oil-producing country.
</P>
<P>
The paper said that ELF is believed to have begun negotiations
with at least two American banks to raise the funds needed to
develop the field which is proved to contain about 400 million
barrels of oil.
</P>
<P>
The field development plan prepared by ELF has been approved
by the Nigerian National Petroleum Corporation and the
development work is expected to begin next year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
