<HEADLINE> Share Prices Extend Loss on Singapore Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, October 2 (Xinhua) -- Share prices kept nose-diving
on the Singapore Stock Market Friday in light dealings as external
worries continued to hit the market and dampen sentiment.
</P>
<P>
Stocks eased from the start of the market following the
overnight tumble on Wall Street and then were driven down by a
morning plunge in Tokyo's Nikkei Index.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said the market lost ground amid mounting concerns over
the health of the global economy.
</P>
<P>
They said local and foreign stocks of banking bore the brunt of
selling on liquidation by institutions.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Straits Times Index (STI) lost 16.03 points to
899.99 points, falling through the support level of 900 points.
</P>
<P>
The total turnover dropped to 91.07 million units valued at
149.23 million Singapore dollars (about 88.50 million U.S.
dollars). Decliners outstripped advancers by 154 to 54 while other
224 were unchanged..
</P>
<P>
ST Engg topped the actives chart with 9.48 million stocks
changing hands. It was followed by Van DH that had 5.00 million
units done. Parkway w98 was next with 4.76 million counters
traded.
</P>
<P>
Elec&AMP;E topped the gainers of the day with a rise of 22 cents to
4.72 U.S. dollars at close . Boustd F moved up 15 cents to 0.70
Singapore dollars. Shangri edged up six cents to end at 1.81
Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, SIA 200 dropped 60 cents to 5.20 Singapore
dollars. SIA F lost 55 cents to finish at 8.20 Singapore dollars.
Asean shed off 50 cents to 3.80 U.S. dollars. 
</P>
