</P>
<P>
-- Five years after Stephen Lawrence was murdered, Sir Paul
Condon, commissioner of the Metropolitan Police in London,
apologized in person Thursday to the black teenager's parents for
failing to catch the killers.
</P>
<P>
Financial Times:
</P>
<P>
-- The severe toll taken on the banking sector by the
near-collapse of Long-Term Capital management and the emerging
market debt crisis became clearer Thursday as one leading bank
announced heavy job cuts, and UBS prepared to jettison several
senior executives. 
</P>
