<HEADLINE> Turkish President Leaves on Visit to Macedonia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, October 2 (Xinhua) -- Turkish President Suleyman
Demirel said Friday that Turkey will continue to exert efforts
for the preservation of independence, sovereignty and territorial
integrity of Macedonia.
</P>
<P>
Before his departure for a two-day official visit to
Macedonia, Demirel said at the Ankara Esenboga Airport that
during his talks with Macedonian President Kiro Gligorov, they
will seek ways to further develop cooperation in the fields of
the economy, transportation, trade, culture and military.
</P>
<P>
This is the second visit of Demirel to Macedonia, a country
located in the heart of southeastern Europe, since he became
president in 1993.
</P>
<P>
"My visit will be a means for disclosing the joint attitudes of
Turkey and Macedonia who have similar concerns regarding the
Kosovo issue," Demirel said, quoted by the semi-official Anatolia
news agency.
</P>
<P>
"We will also discuss Turkish entrepreneurs' contributions to
the road project, called the East-West Corridor, which will link
Varna to Durres in the Adriatic via Scopje," he added.
</P>
<P>
Two agreements in the field of agricultural cooperation and a
new protocol between scientific organizations of the two countries
will be signed during Demirel's visit. 
</P>
