<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pan American Games Bar Male Synchronized Swimmer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, October 1 (Xinhua) -- There will be no barechested
competitors in the synchronized swimming event at the 1999 Pan
American Games, according to reports from Winnipeg, Canada.
</P>
<P>
That's because American synchro star Bill May, who won two
silver medals in the traditionally female sport at the 1998
Goodwill Games, has been ordered out of the pool.
</P>
<P>
Don MacKenzie, president and CEO of the Games to be held in
Winnipeg next summer, said he was "surprised" by the Amateur
Swimming Union of the America's (ASUA) recent ruling to continue
to exclude men from synchro competitions under its
jurisdiction.
</P>
<P>
In making its decision, ASUA deferred to the rules of the
international governing body for aquatic sports known as FINA,
and those of the Olympic Games. Neither allow men to compete in
synchronized swimming. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
