<HEADLINE> New Zealand Stocks Finish Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, October 2 (Xinhua) -- The New Zealand sharemarket
closed lower here Friday.
</P>
<P>
The NZSE40 Index ended 27 points lower at 1,668 with a turnover
of 65 million NZ dollars (32.5 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Among the major leaders, AMP continued to be the biggest loser,
 plumping 80 cents to 2,295 cents, while Carter Holt Harvey
dropped 11 cents to 115 cents, Telecome 8 cents to 735 cents,
Fletcher Paper 5 cents to 96 cents, and Brierley Investments 4
cents to 30 cents.
</P>
<P>
Fletcher Energy kept going against the general trend, gaining
16 cents to 330 cents. Air New Zealand and Fletcher Forest put on
2 cents each to 145 cents and 42 cents respectively. Both Auckland
Airport and Fletcher Building were stable at 180 cents and 183
cents respectively. 
</P>
</TEXT>
