<HEADLINE> Largest U.S. Merged Bank Keeps Old Name </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LOS ANGELES, October 1 (Xinhua) -- The largest bank in the
United States, created by the merger of two banks officially
completed Wednesday, will operate as Bank of America, the new bank
announced Thursday
</P>
<P>
"We believe we have made an excellent choice," said the new
bank, which was created by the merger of Bank of America
(BankAmerica) and NationsBank.
</P>
<P>
The decision followed months of strength analysis of the two
old names. Some 5,000 customers and employees were interviewed and
big bucks were paid to a New York ID consultant.
</P>
<P>
The name of NationsBank was chosen seven years ago, while Bank
of America, based in San Francisco, has been around since 1930.
</P>
<P>
The combined new bank will be headquartered in Charlotte, where
the former principal office of NationsBank was situated, with
NationsBank boss Hugh McColl as chairman and CEO.
</P>
<P>
The surviving 20-person board of directors of the new bank is
comprised of 11 directors from NationsBank and nine from Bank of
America. Bank of America's boss David Coulter is now president of
the new bank.
</P>
<P>
The new bank holds a leading 8 percent share of the nation's
bank deposits and has relationships with 30 million American
households as well as two million businesses around the world.
</P>
</TEXT>
