<HEADLINE> Ukraine Calls for Closer Economic Cooperation with China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, October 1 (Xinhua) -- Ukraine wants to strengthen
economic and trade cooperation with China, Prime Minister Valery
Pustovoitenko told Chinese Ambassador Zhou Xiaopei on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
At a meeting with Zhou on China's National Day, Pustovoitenko
expressed concern over the fall in bilateral trade this year,
noting that great potentials exist in the cooperation between the
two countries.
</P>
<P>
He called for effective measures to maintain the momentum in
bilateral economic and trade cooperation and urged China to expand
cooperation with Ukraine in the fields of metallurgy, chemical
industry, airplane and ship building.
</P>
<P>
Expressing hope to strengthen exchanges with China on economic
reforms, Pustovoitenko said Ukraine is preparing to draw on
China's experience in setting up special economic zones.
</P>
<P>
On impacts of the Russian monetary crisis, he said his
government was taking measures to stabilize the domestic financial
situation.  
