<DOCNO> XIE19981002.0199 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing Experiences Warm Autumn </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, October 2 (Xinhua) -- Beijing is experiencing its
warmest autumn in 62 years.
</P>
<P>
Local residents donned summer clothing on Thursday, this year's
National Day, a day which normally tends to be pleasantly cool.
</P>
<P>
The temperature in Beijing usually drops some 15 degrees
centigrade between September and November.
</P>
<P>
The Beijing Meteorological Observatory reports that this past
September was one of three similar periods in history with average
temperatures above 22 degrees centigrade. Similar September
temperatures were last recorded in 1935.
</P>
<P>
Atmospheric conditions remained stable and the air was somewhat
humid during the month, according to experts from the observatory.
</P>
<P>
Experts here explained that El Nino contributed to the abnormal
climate and noted that research continues to determine what effect
it will have on this winter's weather. 
</P>
</TEXT>
