<HEADLINE> Quake Victims Move to Newly Built Homes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, October 2 (Xinhua) -- Earthquake victims in
Zhangjiakou in north China's Hebei Province have all moved to
their new houses which were built by the local government.
</P>
<P>
Fortunately, the local people, previously residing in makeshift
rooms, were able to begin living in the newly built quake-proof
houses before the winter season begins, local officials said.
</P>
<P>
According to city government statistics, 63,752 rooms were
rebuilt, 184,000 were repaired, and 325 schools were reconstructed
in the quake-hit areas including Zhangbei, Shangyi, Wanquan,
Kangbao and other counties.
</P>
<P>
A disastrous tremor, measuring 6.2 degrees on the Richter
scale, hit the area on January 10 this year.
</P>
<P>
Afterwards, the city went all-out to collect funds for building
new homes for the quake victims. 
