<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rangers Beats Beitar in UEFA Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, October 1 (Xinhua) -- Rangers defeated Beitar
Jerusalem 4-2 in Glasgow on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
With the win, Rangers won 5-3 on aggregate to go through to
the second round of the UEFA Cup.
</P>
<P>
Contributions from two Italians Rino Gattuso and Sergio Porri
ni in the first half ended any danger of an upset at Ibrox
Stadium and further strikes from Jonatan Johansson and Rod
Wallace in the second half sealed an aggregate win.
</P>
<P>
Teenager Gattuso put the Scots ahead in front of 45,610 fans
after just 20 seconds, volleying in a cross from Giovanni van
Bronckhorst.
</P>
<P>
Former Juventus defender Porrini increased the lead in the
25th minute when he rose to bullet in a header from van
Bronckhorst's corner.
</P>
<P>
Beitar fought back with Hungarian striker Lazslo Salloi scor
ing in the 34th minute after a great run down the left by Shitret.
</P>
<P>
Rangers goalkeeper Lionel Charbonnier pulled off two great
saves from another Hungarian, Sandor, to prevent Beitar levelling
it at 2-2 but then Johansson took Rangers 3-1 ahead in the 60th
minute, clipping the ball in from close range to finish off a
fine run by Tony Vidmar.
</P>
<P>
Six minutes later Rod Wallace put the ball in an empty net
after Johannson opened up the Beitar defence.
</P>
<P>
Israel international Eli Ohana went on as a late substitute
and scored with an 80th minute penalty after Shitret was brought
down by Lorenzo Amoruso but by then the visitors had been left
with too much to do. 
</P>
</TEXT>
