<HEADLINE> Rios, Philippoussis Advance for Semi-Final Tie </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, October 1 (Xinhua) -- World number three Marcelo Rios of
Chile and Mark Philippousis of Australia advanced for a
semi-final tie after both defeated their opponents on Thursday in
the Grand Slam Cup tennis Tournament in Munich, Germany.
</P>
<P>
Rios, the highest ranked player in the men's draw, saw off
Spaniard Felix Mantilla 7-6, 7-5 in a close baseliners battle,
while the U.S. finalist Philippousis beat Swede Jonas Bjorkman
4-6, 7-6, 6-1 with his missile aces.
</P>
<P>
After taking the tie break 7-2 in the first set, Rios sealed
victory with a backhand volley to pocket at least 375,000 U.S.
dollars in prize money.
</P>
<P>
Phillippousis, making his first appearance in the lucrative
tournament, came back from one set down and stormed an ace to
claim the tie break 7-1 in the second.
</P>
<P>
He went on for a 4-0 lead in the decisive set and fired aces
on his way for the quarter-final win. 
</P>
</TEXT>
