<DATE_TIME> 1998-10-02 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pistons Names Head and Ociepka to Coaching Staff </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, October 1 (Xinhua) -- Alvin Gentry, preparing for
his first full season as head coach of the Detriot Pistons, has
named Gar Heard and Bob Ociepka to his coaching staff, the club
announced today in Detriot.
</P>
<P>
Heard and Ociepka join currnet Pistons assistant John Hammond,
who has been in the organization for the past five season.
</P>
<P>
"I'm very pleased to be able to add Gar and Bobby to our
staff," said Gentry. "Together with John they have nearly 30
years of NBA coaching experience and I know we will work well
together as a group."
</P>
<P>
Heard joins the Piston after spending a year as an assistnat
under Larry Brown in Philadelphia. He began his 11-year coaching
career in Dallas and served as the Mavericks' head coach for the
second half of the 1992-93 season following the firing of Richie
Adubato.
</P>
<P>
Ociepka was the Orlando Magic's advance professional scout
last season. He has been coaching in the NBA since 1989 when he
was hired out of high school by the Indian Pacers. He stayed with
the Pacers through 1993 before joining the Los Angeles Clippers
for three years.
</P>
<P>
The NBA is currently locking out the players and the labor
dispute has threatened to delay the start of the regular season.
</P>
</TEXT>
